-- Sugar Awaiting Loading at Brazil’s Ports Falls in Past Week
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2013-03-28T09:36:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-28/sugar-awaiting-loading-at-brazil-s-ports-falls-in-past-week.html
The amount of sugar awaiting
loading at ports in top producer  Brazil  dropped to 1.04 million
metric tons, according to figures e-mailed yesterday by Williams
Servicos Maritimos Ltda.  That’s down from 1.36 million tons a week earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Claudia Carpenter in London at 
